# Korvin — Cursor Rules
# Injected into every AI request for this repo.

## Authoritative architecture
- Node.js gateway: src/openclaw/gateway.js
- Telegram bot: src/openclaw/telegram-bot.js
- FastAPI dashboard: src/dashboard/main.py
- Memory layer: src/hermes/memory.py
- Voice: src/voice/voice.py
- Ports: LiteLLM=4000, Dashboard=3002, Cloudflare Tunnel only
- All services bind to 127.0.0.1 — never 0.0.0.0

## Never infer architecture from README — always read source files first

## Output rules — NEVER include in any generated content
- IP addresses of any kind
- API keys, key fragments, or key-looking strings
- Contents of config.json or korvin.env
- Real system usernames beyond what README already documents
- Actual secret values — always use YOUR_KEY_HERE placeholders

## Stack
- Python 3.12 (dashboard, memory, voice)
- Node.js 22 (gateway, Telegram bot)
- SQLite/FTS5 (memory)
- LiteLLM (model routing)
- Cloudflare Zero Trust (tunnel + access)
- Whisper tiny.en (STT)
- Kokoro TTS, voice=bm_lewis

## Code style
- No em dashes in any output
- Surgical edits only — do not rewrite files that dont need changing
- Flag security-relevant changes explicitly before applying them
